Interface BooleanMatrix

All Known Implementing Classes:
ArrayMatrix, BitMatrix, ListMatrix, SparseMatrix
public interface BooleanMatrix
An m x n matrix of boolean values. When adding a value at position (r,c), if r >= m or c >= n, then new rows and/or columns are automatically added, filled with the default value of false, and then the new value is stored.
Author:
Dr. Lillis

    • toggle

      void toggle(int row, int col) throws IndexOutOfBoundsException
      Changes the element at the specified position. If the current value is true it is changed to false. If the current value is false it is changed to true.
      Parameters:
      row - row index of the element to be changed
      col - column index of the element to be changed
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - if either index is out of range (row < 0 || col < 0 || row >= getNumberRows() || col >= getNumberCols())

    • getTruePositions

      int[][] getTruePositions()
      Returns the indices of the elements whose value is true. The indices are returned in a P x 2 array of integers, where P is the number of elements with a value of true. Each row in the returned array contains the row and column index of an element with a value of true. The returned array is sorted in increasing order by row and column. This method should call the getPositions(boolean value) method.
      Returns:
      the indices of all elements whose value is true

    • getFalsePositions

      int[][] getFalsePositions()
      Returns the indices of the elements whose value is false. The indices are returned in a P x 2 array of integers, where P is the number of elements with a value of false. Each row in the returned array contains the row and column index of an element with a value of false. The returned array is sorted in increasing order by row and column. This method should call the getPositions(boolean value) method.
      Returns:
      the indices of all elements whose value is false

    • getPositions

      int[][] getPositions(boolean value)
      Returns the indices of the elements whose value matches the parameter. The indices are returned in a P x 2 array of integers, where P is the number of elements whose value matches the parameter. Each row in the returned array contains the row and column index of an element whose value matches the parameter. The returned array is sorted in increasing order by row and column. This method should call the getPositions(boolean value) method.
      Parameters:
      value - the value used to determine which pairs of indices to return
      Returns:
      the indices of all elements whose value matches the parameter
